WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:11.400
Good day, bad day, by Paul Shipton. Penguin Active Reading Easy Start.

00:11.400 --> 00:24.280
Mike gets a new job and moves from his small town to Boston. He likes the job, and he likes

00:24.280 --> 00:37.840
his new apartment. He likes Boston. There is only one problem. He doesn't meet many new people.

00:37.840 --> 00:53.720
This weekend, Mike's sister, Carrie, is visiting her brother. Do you have many new friends

00:53.720 --> 01:02.680
here? She asks him. Not many, Mike says.

01:02.680 --> 01:18.200
I'm worried about you, Carrie says. You're always worried about me, Mike says. On Saturday morning,

01:18.200 --> 01:35.720
they go out. Let's go into town, Mike says. There's a bus stop near here. But Carrie sees a sign in a

01:35.720 --> 01:55.320
window. Visit Rosie, the fortune teller. No, she says. Let's go in there. Mike isn't happy about this.

01:55.320 --> 02:14.520
He doesn't believe in fortune tellers. But Carrie says, please, Mike, I love fortune tellers. Wait, Carrie,

02:14.520 --> 02:30.640
but she is going into the house and Mike can't stop her. He goes in after her. A woman is sitting at a

02:30.640 --> 02:52.320
table in a small room. This is Rosie, the fortune teller. Who is first? The woman asks. I am, Carrie says.

02:52.320 --> 03:13.600
The two women go into a room at the back of the house. Mike sits and waits. After some time, Carrie comes back with a big smile on her face.

03:14.160 --> 03:42.600
Now you go, she says to her brother. Mike isn't very happy about this, but he goes into the back room. It is very dark. Rosie smiles and puts some cards on the table in front of her.

03:43.600 --> 04:09.600
She looks at them for a long time. She isn't smiling now. What's the problem, Mike asks? It is not a good day for you today, she says.

04:10.600 --> 04:35.600
Mike doesn't like this. Why not? He asks. I can see a black cat, a yellow dog and a white bird. Be very careful.

04:35.600 --> 04:55.600
On the street, Carrie asks Mike about the fortune teller. A cat, a dog and a bird, she asks. Are you worried?

04:55.600 --> 05:10.600
No. I don't believe it, Mike says. Fortune tellers are always wrong, but Carrie isn't listening to him.

05:10.600 --> 05:24.600
Mike, she says, look at that. There is a cat near them, a black cat.

05:25.600 --> 05:51.600
Remember Rosie's warning, Carrie says. Let's go across the street. Quick! I am not worried about a little black cat, Mike says, but he walks across the road with Carrie.

05:51.600 --> 06:12.600
There, a man is washing a cafe window with a bucket of water. Suddenly, the bucket falls. All of the water in it falls too. On, Mike.

06:12.600 --> 06:29.600
I'm sorry. The man says. Remember the fortune tellers warning, Carrie says quietly. Her eyes are big.

06:29.600 --> 06:44.600
Look at the name on the sign. The black cat cafe. I do not believe in fortune tellers, Mike says.

06:44.600 --> 07:10.600
But look at me. Let's go home. But then Carrie says, no. Mike, look. Mike looks and sees a big dog, a big yellow dog.

07:10.600 --> 07:27.600
It is running at him. Mike can't believe his eyes. Oh no, he thinks. Is the fortune tellers warning right?

07:27.600 --> 07:46.600
But the dog doesn't stop. It runs past him. There is a big smile on Mike's face. Now do you believe me? Mike wants some food now.

07:46.600 --> 07:57.600
He buys a hot dog on the street. But Carrie is thinking about the fortune teller.

07:58.600 --> 08:12.600
Wait, she says. A hot dog. Maybe that's the dog in the fortune tellers warning.

08:13.600 --> 08:30.600
Yes, but it isn't yellow, Mike says. Mike is looking at his sister and he doesn't see the little boy near him.

08:30.600 --> 08:49.600
Be careful. The boy's mother says. But Mike walks into the boy and a toy falls from the boy's hands. It hits the road and breaks.

08:49.600 --> 09:01.600
The boy looks down at the little parts of the toy. He is very unhappy. The boy's mother is angry.

09:02.600 --> 09:10.600
Toys are very expensive, she says to Mike.

09:11.600 --> 09:21.600
I'm sorry, Mike says. Here, please take this money for a new toy.

09:22.600 --> 09:32.600
But Carrie is looking at the boy's old toy. Look, Mike, she says.

09:33.600 --> 09:46.600
The toy is a little yellow dog. Mike's face is white. Now he is worried too.

09:46.600 --> 09:54.600
Now do you believe the fortune teller? Carrie asks.

09:55.600 --> 10:04.600
Maybe Mike says quietly. He is walking quickly now.

10:05.600 --> 10:16.600
Where are we going? Carrie asks. Home, he says. He looks up.

10:17.600 --> 10:28.600
What are you looking for? Carrie asks. But she knows the answer. Her brother is worried.

10:29.600 --> 10:42.600
He is looking for a white bird. Suddenly, Mike hears a noise. He looks behind him.

10:43.600 --> 10:53.600
A woman is running after him. Excuse me. The woman calls.

10:54.600 --> 11:11.600
Yes, Mike says. My name's Sally. The woman says. I'm new here. The black cat cafe is my cafe.

11:12.600 --> 11:21.600
She looks at Mike's shirt. I'm very sorry about that bucket of water.

11:22.600 --> 11:34.600
My friend is working at the cafe today. He isn't always very careful. That's okay, Mike says.

11:35.600 --> 11:43.600
It is hot today. Sally smiles at him.

11:44.600 --> 11:50.600
She has a beautiful, friendly smile, Mike thinks.

11:51.600 --> 12:00.600
Listen, he says. Maybe we can go out to a movie this evening?

12:01.600 --> 12:08.600
Okay, yes, Sally says. Let's meet at the cafe.

12:11.600 --> 12:18.600
Sally is walking back to the cafe, but suddenly Carrie calls to her.

12:20.600 --> 12:27.600
Wait, Sally, she says. What's your family name?

12:28.600 --> 12:31.600
Sally looks back.

12:32.600 --> 12:40.600
Swan, she says. My name is Sally Swan.

12:41.600 --> 12:51.600
And then she goes into her cafe. Mike looks at Carrie, and Carrie looks at Mike.

12:52.600 --> 13:07.600
That's bad, Carrie says. That's very bad. A swan is a bird, and it's usually white.

13:08.600 --> 13:18.600
It's part three of your warning from the fortune teller. You can't go to a movie with Sally.

13:19.600 --> 13:29.600
But Mike isn't worried. He is putting his hot dog down. He stands and waits.

13:30.600 --> 13:34.600
Carrie can't believe her eyes.

13:35.600 --> 13:39.600
What are you doing? She asks.

13:40.600 --> 13:44.600
Suddenly she hears a noise.

13:45.600 --> 13:55.600
A big seagull flies down. It takes the hot dog, and then it flies away.

13:56.600 --> 14:01.600
I don't understand, Carrie says.

14:02.600 --> 14:05.600
Now you have no food.

14:06.600 --> 14:09.600
Mike is smiling.

14:10.600 --> 14:15.600
That seagull is a white bird, he says.

14:16.600 --> 14:21.600
Now the fortune teller's warning is right.

14:22.600 --> 14:28.600
A black cat, a yellow dog, and a white bird.

14:29.600 --> 14:35.600
And now I can go to a movie with Sally.

14:36.600 --> 14:38.600
Carrie smiles too.

14:40.600 --> 14:45.600
That fortune teller is good, she says.

14:46.600 --> 14:49.600
Why, Mike asks.

14:50.600 --> 14:57.600
Look at this. This is from Rosie, for me.

14:58.600 --> 15:01.600
Thank you.

